724635f-a.text:
West Street, Hubert, to Laight Street, (Before reconstruction).
President Borough of Manhattan.
June 9, 1912.
NEG. # 4564
724635f-a.folder: West Street & Hubert Street, Manhattan, NY

724634f-a.text:
West Street, north from but not including Hubert Street.
About 1919.
724634f-a.folder: West Street & Hubert Street, Manhattan, NY

724633f-a.text:
(1)
West Street, north from Bubert Street, showing foundation work for the extension of the West Side Express Highway. For an account of same, see the N.Y. Times of November 12, 1937. Buildings on the
right, line the east side of this street.
July 28, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
N(eg ~2968
(2)
One block northward, from Laight Street. Piers on the left abut on the North River. The 9-story structure appearing on the right is No. 260-262 West Street, at the S.E. corner of Vestry Street (upon
which it also bears Nos. 67-73).
July 28, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
